s($,"aKT","avR",()=>{var q="Pre-Takeoff & General Safety",p="Seguridad Pre-Despegue",o="Emergency Scenarios",n="Escenarios de Emergencia",m="Exits & Evacuation",l="Salidas y Evacuaci\xf3n",k="Onboard Gear",j="Equipo a Bordo",i=A.ai("w<Io>")
return A.c([A.cJ(q,p,1,"\ud83d\udd12",1,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Only during takeoff and landing","Solo durante despegue y aterrizaje"),A.a7(!0,"At all times when seated","En todo momento cuando est\xe9s sentado"),A.a7(!1,"Only if turbulence is expected","Solo si se espera turbulencia"),A.a7(!1,"Never required at cruising altitude","Nunca requerido a altitud de crucero")],i),"When should your seatbelt be fastened?","\xbfCu\xe1ndo debe estar abrochado tu cintur\xf3n de seguridad?","FAA recommends keeping your seatbelt fastened at all times to protect against clear-air turbulence, which can occur suddenly.","La FAA recomienda mantener el cintur\xf3n abrochado en todo momento para protegerse contra la turbulencia en aire claro, que puede ocurrir repentinamente."),A.cJ(q,p,1,"\ud83e\uddf3",2,A.c([A.a7(!1,"It reduces fuel consumption","Reduce el consumo de combustible"),A.a7(!0,"To prevent it from blocking evacuation routes","Para evitar que obstruya las rutas de evacuaci\xf3n"),A.a7(!1,"It improves aircraft balance","Mejora el equilibrio de la aeronave"),A.a7(!1,"Airline policy only","Solo pol\xedtica de la aerol\xednea")],i),"Why must your tray table be stowed for takeoff?","\xbfPor qu\xe9 debe recogerse la bandeja para el despegue?","A stowed tray table ensures clear evacuation paths and prevents debris from becoming projectiles during turbulence or emergency maneuvers.","Una bandeja recogida asegura rutas de evacuaci\xf3n claras y previene que los objetos se conviertan en proyectiles durante turbulencia."),A.cJ(q,p,1,"\ud83d\udcf1",3,A.c([A.a7(!1,"To save battery power","Para ahorrar energ\xeda de bater\xeda"),A.a7(!0,"To prevent interference with cockpit avionics","Para prevenir interferencia con los sistemas de avi\xf3nica"),A.a7(!1,"To prevent data roaming charges","Para prevenir cargos de roaming"),A.a7(!1,"It has no technical purpose","No tiene prop\xf3sito t\xe9cnico")],i),'Why do we enable "Airplane Mode" on phones?','\xbfPor qu\xe9 activamos el "Modo Avi\xf3n" en tel\xe9fonos?',"Airplane Mode prevents RF emissions that could interfere with critical navigation and communication systems in the cockpit.","El Modo Avi\xf3n previene emisiones que podr\xedan interferir con sistemas cr\xedticos de navegaci\xf3n y comunicaci\xf3n en la cabina de mando."),A.cJ(q,p,1,"\ud83e\ude9f",4,A.c([A.a7(!1,"For passenger comfort","Para comodidad del pasajero"),A.a7(!0,"To allow your eyes to adjust for emergency visibility","Para permitir que tus ojos se adapten para visibilidad de emergencia"),A.a7(!1,"To improve aerodynamics","Para mejorar la aerodin\xe1mica"),A.a7(!1,"There is no safety reason","No hay raz\xf3n de seguridad")],i),"Why keep window blinds open during takeoff and landing?","\xbfPor qu\xe9 mantener las persianas abiertas durante despegue y aterrizaje?","Eye adaptation is critical during evacuation. If cabin lights fail, eyes adjusted to outside light can help identify exits.","La adaptaci\xf3n de los ojos es cr\xedtica durante la evacuaci\xf3n. Si las luces fallan, los ojos adaptados pueden ayudar a identificar salidas."),A.cJ(q,p,1,"\u25b2",5,A.c([A.a7(!1,"A decoration","Una decoraci\xf3n"),A.a7(!0,"A marker for the flight crew to check wing flaps and ice","Una marca para que la tripulaci\xf3n verifique los alerones y hielo"),A.a7(!1,"A pressure relief vent","Una ventila de alivio de presi\xf3n"),A.a7(!1,"A camera for surveillance","Una c\xe1mara de vigilancia")],i),"What is the small black triangle above your window?","\xbfQu\xe9 es el peque\xf1o tri\xe1ngulo negro sobre tu ventana?","The black triangle is a reference point (chine) for flight crew to visually inspect the wing during flight for ice accumulation and mechanical issues.","El tri\xe1ngulo negro es un punto de referencia para que la tripulaci\xf3n inspeccione visualmente el ala durante el vuelo."),A.cJ(q,p,2,"\u26a0\ufe0f",6,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Recline the seat to find it","Reclina el asiento para encontrarlo"),A.a7(!1,"Adjust the seat mechanism to retrieve it","Ajusta el mecanismo del asiento para recuperarlo"),A.a7(!0,"Notify a flight attendant - DO NOT move the seat","Notifica a una azafata - NO muevas el asiento"),A.a7(!1,"Leave it - it will be found later","D\xe9jalo - ser\xe1 encontrado m\xe1s tarde")],i),"Your phone falls into the seat mechanism. What do you do?","\xbfTu tel\xe9fono cae en el mecanismo del asiento? \xbfQu\xe9 haces?","Lithium batteries in phones can be crushed by seat mechanisms, causing fires. Flight attendants have procedures to safely retrieve items.","Las bater\xedas de litio en tel\xe9fonos pueden ser aplastadas por mecanismos del asiento, causando incendios. Las azafatas tienen procedimientos seguros."),A.cJ(o,n,2,"\ud83d\udca8",7,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Near the ceiling","Cerca del techo"),A.a7(!1,"In the middle of the cabin","En el medio de la cabina"),A.a7(!0,"Near the floor","Cerca del suelo"),A.a7(!1,"At the emergency exits","En las salidas de emergencia")],i),"If smoke fills the cabin, where is the cleanest air?","\xbfSi el humo llena la cabina, d\xf3nde est\xe1 el aire m\xe1s limpio?","Smoke rises. Fresh air enters near floor level from the fuselage ventilation system. Always crouch or crawl low.","El humo sube. El aire fresco entra cerca del suelo. Siempre ag\xe1chate o arrastra por el suelo."),A.cJ(o,n,1,"\ud83d\ude37",8,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Your child","Tu hijo"),A.a7(!0,"Yourself","T\xfa mismo"),A.a7(!1,"An elderly passenger","Un pasajero mayor"),A.a7(!1,"A flight attendant","Una azafata")],i),"In a decompression, who gets the oxygen mask first?","\xbfEn una descompresi\xf3n, qui\xe9n obtiene la m\xe1scara de ox\xedgeno primero?","You must secure your own oxygen first. You cannot help others if you are incapacitated.","Debes asegurar tu propio ox\xedgeno primero. No puedes ayudar a otros si est\xe1s incapacitado."),A.cJ(o,n,2,"\ud83d\udd25",9,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Yes, always","S\xed, siempre"),A.a7(!1,"Only if the fire is small","Solo si el incendio es peque\xf1o"),A.a7(!0,"No - oxygen feeds fire and concentrates heat","No - el ox\xedgeno alimenta el fuego y concentra el calor"),A.a7(!1,"It depends on the location","Depende de la ubicaci\xf3n")],i),"Should you use oxygen during an active cabin fire?","\xbfDebes usar ox\xedgeno durante un incendio activo en la cabina?","Oxygen masks must never be used near fires. Evacuate immediately and crawl to an exit.","Las m\xe1scaras de ox\xedgeno nunca deben usarse cerca de incendios. Evac\xfaa inmediatamente."),A.cJ(o,n,2,"\ud83d\udcbb",10,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Pack it carefully in your carry-on","Emp\xe1calo cuidadosamente en tu bolso"),A.a7(!1,"Hold it while evacuating","Sostenlo mientras evac\xfaas"),A.a7(!0,"Drop it and evacuate immediately","Su\xe9ltalo y evac\xfaa inmediatamente"),A.a7(!1,"Ask a flight attendant to hold it","P\xeddele a una azafata que lo sostunga")],i),"Fire alarm sounds and you have your laptop. What do you do?","\xbfLa alarma de incendio suena y tienes tu laptop? \xbfQu\xe9 haces?","In an emergency evacuation, every second counts. Leave all belongings behind. Your life is infinitely more valuable than any item.","En una evacuaci\xf3n de emergencia, cada segundo cuenta. Deja todos tus pertenencias. Tu vida es m\xe1s valiosa."),A.cJ(o,n,1,"\ud83d\udec2",11,A.c([A.a7(!1,"To stay comfortable during rough air","Para mantenerse c\xf3modo durante aire turbulento"),A.a7(!0,"To reduce flailing and impact force","Para reducir el movimiento sin control y la fuerza de impacto"),A.a7(!1,"To prepare for takeoff","Para prepararse para el despegue"),A.a7(!1,"To prevent motion sickness","Para prevenir mareos")],i),'What is the purpose of the "Brace" position?','\xbfCu\xe1l es el prop\xf3sito de la posici\xf3n de "Protecci\xf3n"?',"The brace position (hands on head, elbows against ribs) protects your head and chest during emergency landings or crashes.","La posici\xf3n de protecci\xf3n protege tu cabeza y pecho durante aterrizajes de emergencia o accidentes."),A.cJ(o,n,2,"\ud83d\udc60",12,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Passenger comfort","Comodidad del pasajero"),A.a7(!1,"They slow down the evacuation","Ralentizan la evacuaci\xf3n"),A.a7(!0,"They can puncture the slide, causing deflation","Pueden perforar la rampa, causando desinflamaci\xf3n"),A.a7(!1,"They damage the shoes","Da\xf1an los zapatos")],i),"Why must high heels be removed before using an evacuation slide?","\xbfPor qu\xe9 deben removerse los tacones altos antes de usar una rampa de evacuaci\xf3n?","Modern evacuation slides are made of coated fabric. A puncture causes rapid deflation, creating a dangerous situation for others below.","Las rampas de evacuaci\xf3n son de tela. Una perforaci\xf3n causa desinflamaci\xf3n r\xe1pida, peligrosa para otros."),A.cJ(m,l,2,"\u23f1\ufe0f",13,A.c([A.a7(!1,"30 seconds","30 segundos"),A.a7(!1,"60 seconds","60 segundos"),A.a7(!0,"90 seconds","90 segundos"),A.a7(!1,"120 seconds","120 segundos")],i),"How long do manufacturers have to prove full evacuation?","\xbfCu\xe1nto tiempo tienen los fabricantes para demostrar evacuaci\xf3n completa?","FAA/EASA certification requires aircraft to evacuate all passengers in 90 seconds using only 50% of exits.","La certificaci\xf3n FAA/EASA requiere evacuar a todos los pasajeros en 90 segundos usando solo 50% de las salidas."),A.cJ(m,l,2,"\ud83d\udeaa",14,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Yes, if the aisle is clear","S\xed, si el pasillo est\xe1 despejado"),A.a7(!1,"Only small bags","Solo bolsas peque\xf1as"),A.a7(!0,"No - it creates a trip hazard","No - crea un peligro de tropiezo"),A.a7(!1,"Only if the flight is short","Solo si el vuelo es corto")],i),"If seated in an exit row, can you put bags under the seat in front?","\xbfSi est\xe1s sentado en una fila de salida, puedes poner bolsas debajo del asiento frontal?","Exit rows must be completely clear of obstacles. Even small bags can trip evacuating passengers, potentially causing injuries or deaths.","Las filas de salida deben estar completamente despejadas. Incluso bolsas peque\xf1as pueden causar tropiezos durante la evacuaci\xf3n."),A.cJ(m,l,1,"\ud83d\udd04",15,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Always counterclockwise","Siempre en sentido antihorario"),A.a7(!0,"Follow the arrows on the door","Sigue las flechas en la puerta"),A.a7(!1,"Pull it outward","T\xedralo hacia afuera"),A.a7(!1,"Push down on the handle","Presiona el manija hacia abajo")],i),"How do you know which way to turn an emergency exit door?","\xbfC\xf3mo sabes en qu\xe9 direcci\xf3n girar la puerta de salida de emergencia?","All emergency exit doors have printed arrows showing the correct direction to open them. Follow these instructions exactly.","Todas las puertas de salida de emergencia tienen flechas que muestran la direcci\xf3n correcta. Sigue estas instrucciones exactamente."),A.cJ(m,l,2,"\ud83d\udedd",16,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Arms outstretched","Brazos extendidos"),A.a7(!1,"Arms raised above head","Brazos levantados sobre la cabeza"),A.a7(!0,"Arms crossed over chest","Brazos cruzados sobre el pecho"),A.a7(!1,"Hands on the slide","Manos en la rampa")],i),"When jumping into a slide, what arm position is safest?","\xbfCuando saltas a una rampa, qu\xe9 posici\xf3n de brazo es m\xe1s segura?","Crossing arms over chest protects your torso and allows faster movement down the slide. Outstretched arms can catch or break.","Los brazos cruzados protegen tu torso y permiten movimiento m\xe1s r\xe1pido. Los brazos extendidos pueden engancharse o romperse."),A.cJ(m,l,2,"\ud83c\udf2b\ufe0f",17,A.c([A.a7(!1,"A loud alarm","Una alarma fuerte"),A.a7(!1,"A temperature change","Un cambio de temperatura"),A.a7(!0,"Floor lighting changes color (red or more intense)","La iluminaci\xf3n del piso cambia de color (rojo o m\xe1s intenso)"),A.a7(!1,"You hear crew members","Escuchas a miembros de la tripulaci\xf3n")],i),"If visibility is zero, what tells you you've reached an exit?","\xbfSi la visibilidad es cero, qu\xe9 te indica que alcanzaste una salida?","All aircraft have floor-level lighting that changes color near exits\u2014typically red or a brighter color\u2014to guide evacuees in zero visibility conditions.","Todos los aviones tienen iluminaci\xf3n a nivel del suelo que cambia de color cerca de salidas para guiar a los evacuados."),A.cJ(m,l,2,"\ud83d\udd25",18,A.c([A.a7(!1,"To ensure good weather","Para asegurar buen clima"),A.a7(!1,"To see if anyone is below","Para ver si hay alguien abajo"),A.a7(!0,"To ensure there is no fire or water on the other side","Para asegurar que no hay fuego o agua del otro lado"),A.a7(!1,"To signal for help","Para se\xf1alar pidiendo ayuda")],i),"Why check the window before opening an emergency exit?","\xbfPor qu\xe9 verificar la ventana antes de abrir una salida de emergencia?","Opening an exit to a raging fire or water would be catastrophic. Always check the window/door area first for external hazards.","Abrir una salida hacia un incendio o agua ser\xeda catastr\xf3fico. Siempre verifica primero si hay peligros externos."),A.cJ(k,j,2,"\ud83e\uddba",19,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Immediately when you sit down","Inmediatamente cuando te sientas"),A.a7(!1,'When the "fasten seatbelts" sign illuminates',"Cuando se enciende el signo de abrocharse los cinturones"),A.a7(!0,"Only after exiting the aircraft","Solo despu\xe9s de salir de la aeronave"),A.a7(!1,"When the plane is on the water","Cuando el avi\xf3n est\xe1 en el agua")],i),"When do you inflate your life vest?","\xbfCu\xe1ndo inflas tu chaleco salvavidas?","Inflating your vest inside the cabin can trap you or prevent you from exiting. Inflate only after you are outside the aircraft.","Inflar tu chaleco dentro de la cabina puede atraparte. Infla solo despu\xe9s de salir de la aeronave."),A.cJ(k,j,1,"\ud83d\udd26",20,A.c([A.a7(!1,"For comfort","Para comodidad"),A.a7(!0,"To signal rescuers in dark or poor visibility","Para se\xf1alar a los rescatistas en condiciones oscuras o de poca visibilidad"),A.a7(!1,"To keep you awake in the water","Para mantenerte despierto en el agua"),A.a7(!1,"To scare away marine animals","Para espantar animales marinos")],i),"Why does every life vest have a whistle and light?","\xbfPor qu\xe9 cada chaleco salvavidas tiene un silbato y una luz?","The whistle carries for miles over water; the light makes you visible to rescue aircraft and ships. Use them conservatively to preserve battery and voice.","El silbato se escucha a millas sobre el agua; la luz te hace visible. \xdasalos conservadoramente."),A.cJ(k,j,2,"\ud83d\udccb",21,A.c([A.a7(!1,"On the flight attendant's manifest","En el manifiesto de la azafata"),A.a7(!1,"The airline's website","El sitio web de la aerol\xednea"),A.a7(!0,"The Safety Card in your seat pocket","La Tarjeta de Seguridad en tu bolsillo"),A.a7(!1,"You have to ask a flight attendant","Tienes que preguntarle a una azafata")],i),"Where can you find your specific aircraft's exit layout?","\xbfD\xf3nde puedes encontrar el dise\xf1o espec\xedfico de salidas de tu aeronave?","The Safety Card shows YOUR aircraft model and exact exit locations. Review it before takeoff. It could save your life.","La Tarjeta de Seguridad muestra tu modelo de aeronave. Rev\xedsala antes del despegue."),A.cJ(k,j,1,"\ud83d\udc67",22,A.c([A.a7(!1,"12 years old","12 a\xf1os"),A.a7(!0,"15 years old","15 a\xf1os"),A.a7(!1,"18 years old","18 a\xf1os"),A.a7(!1,"Any age if supervised","Cualquier edad si est\xe1 supervisado")],i),"What is the minimum age to sit in an exit row?","\xbfCu\xe1l es la edad m\xednima para sentarse en una fila de salida?","FAA regulations prohibit passengers under 15 from sitting in exit rows. This ensures they can open emergency doors and assist in evacuation if needed.","La regulaci\xf3n FAA proh\xedbe pasajeros menores de 15 a\xf1os en filas de salida. Asegura que puedan abrir puertas de emergencia si es necesario."),A.cJ(k,j,2,"\ud83e\uddf5",23,A.c([A.a7(!1,"In the overhead bin","En el compartimiento superior"),A.a7(!1,"Behind the seat in front of you","Detr\xe1s del asiento frente a ti"),A.a7(!0,"Under or between your seat","Debajo o entre tu asiento"),A.a7(!1,"At the emergency exit","En la salida de emergencia")],i),"Where is your life vest usually located?","\xbfD\xf3nde se encuentra generalmente tu chaleco salvavidas?","Life vests are stored under or between seats on aircraft with water routes. Know where yours is before you need it.","Los chalecos salvavidas se almacenan bajo o entre los asientos. Sabe d\xf3nde est\xe1 el tuyo antes de necesitarlo."),A.cJ(k,j,1,"\ud83d\udc76",24,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Yes, close contact is safer","S\xed, el contacto cercano es m\xe1s seguro"),A.a7(!0,"No - approved car seats are required by FAA","No - los asientos de auto aprobados son requeridos por la FAA"),A.a7(!1,"It does not matter","No importa"),A.a7(!1,"Only for flights longer than 4 hours","Solo para vuelos m\xe1s largos de 4 horas")],i),"Is a lap-child safer than a child in an approved car seat?","\xbfUn ni\xf1o en regazo es m\xe1s seguro que un ni\xf1o en un asiento de auto aprobado?","The FAA strongly recommends separate seats for children in approved car seats. Lap-holding provides no protection during turbulence or emergency maneuvers.","La FAA recomienda fuertemente asientos separados para ni\xf1os. Sostener en regazo no proporciona protecci\xf3n."),A.cJ(k,j,2,"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\u2708\ufe0f",25,A.c([A.a7(!1,"Serving food and beverages","Servir comida y bebidas"),A.a7(!1,"Checking boarding passes","Verificar tarjetas de embarque"),A.a7(!0,"Safety and evacuation coordination","Coordinaci\xf3n de seguridad y evacuaci\xf3n"),A.a7(!1,"Entertainment management","Gesti\xf3n del entretenimiento")],i),"What is the primary role of flight attendants?","\xbfCu\xe1l es el rol principal de los asistentes de vuelo?","Flight attendants are trained safety professionals first. Their primary duty is passenger safety and emergency response, not service.","Los asistentes de vuelo son profesionales de seguridad entrenados. Su deber principal es la seguridad y respuesta de emergencia.")],A.ai("w<Ip>"))})
